  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Recovery from Cholera in Three Urban Centres</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To support 150,000 women, men and children in communities and institutions in  three urban centres,  Mount  Darwin, Mudzi and Lower Guruve  to recover from the 2008 -09 cholera epidemic and years of under investment in WASH, through the emergency rehabilitation of Water and Sanitation (WATSAN) infrastructure and the promotion of community health and hygiene.  There is also a strong component of  capacity  building of  local partners. The project is  funded by AUSAID through Oxfam Australia.</narrative>
  </description>
